   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">General storage conditions:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Storage temperature between +15°C (59°F) and +40°C
(104°F).</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">30-70% relative humidity.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">No direct sunlight.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">No direct storage on the floor, alongside walls, in front of
radiators or other heat sources.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">No conductive dust allowed (As per IEC 721-3-3).</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
      </div>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Storage Inspection Plan</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">During
long time storage the parts and packing needs to be inspected regularly.
It is recommended to inspect the packing every 6 month and the part
every year.</p>
            <note class="- topic/note ">If the packing is opened to visually inspect
the part, the packing must be closed to its original received state
before continued storage.</note>
            <p class="- topic/p ">The packing inspection should cover:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Visual inspection of the packing.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the storage condition are followed.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the ESD protection or any extra required protection
is used.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">If necessary, replace any desiccant or drying agent.</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
               <note class="- topic/note ">If the packing inspection reveals any irregularities or
damage to the packing immediate action is required to determine if
it continued long-term storage is possible. Detailed inspection of
the part is required, and remedies to the storage condition or packing
might be needed.</note>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">The part inspection should cover:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Visual inspection of the part for any signs of aging.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">If necessary, perform any required refurbishment.</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
